# How to use macOS Catalina as an installer boot drive
Once macOS Catalina is installed on your external drive, you can boot up and install any Mac with the drive plugged into it.

Turn off the Mac you want to install macOS Catalina with the bootable drive.
Connect the external drive to your Mac via the USB port.
Turn on your Mac.
Hold down the Option key when you hear the startup chime.
Select the external drive with macOS Catalina on it from the list of systems to start up your computer.
The installation process will begin. Follow the steps to install macOS Catalina onto your Mac or partitioned hard drive.
